video_title: Super Bowl LX Opening Performance by Green Day
author: @NormaJuarezRivera
comment_text:
I attended a Green Day concert approximately 11 years ago. Towards the end of it, Billy gave a very moving speech about unity, compassion and empathy, but the statement that was engraved in my heart and soul was, “You have to take stand for the little guy in the back, you may be his only voice”.  My admiration for him and the band as the great artists they are, transformed into an admiration for his humility and humanity.

That line follows me to this day, and I share it with my daughter.

comment_text: Thts sad but okay, fair enough. But I’d say that when you go to a show like this as a photographer, you can generally assume that someone higher up in the production has a camera somewhere and that you might be in their way. As a photojournalist, I constantly look around me, in a full 360-degree awareness. From that camera position, I’d also say he probably didn’t get a single usable shot anyway. it’s something you can keep in mind. Having that awareness and showing a bit of respect for the other people working around you is just part of the job.
